WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.199 --> 00:00:09.198
(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:58.586 --> 00:01:02.890
♪

3
00:01:45.332 --> 00:01:47.336
(theme concludes)

4
00:01:54.742 --> 00:01:56.741
(birds chirping)

5
00:01:56.742 --> 00:01:59.409
(ambient nature sounds)

6
00:01:59.410 --> 00:02:02.451
(light music playing)

7
00:02:04.251 --> 00:02:06.255
(raven caws)

8
00:02:13.494 --> 00:02:15.493
♪

9
00:02:15.494 --> 00:02:17.532
(wind blowing)

10
00:02:23.937 --> 00:02:26.941
speaker: <i>Duty is sacrifice.</i>

11
00:02:28.042 --> 00:02:30.475
<i>It eclipses all things.</i>

12
00:02:30.476 --> 00:02:32.147
<i>even blood.</i>

13
00:02:33.813 --> 00:02:37.018
<i>All men of honor
must pay its price.</i>

14
00:02:41.622 --> 00:02:45.289
<i>The North owes a great
duty to the Seven Kingdoms.</i>

15
00:02:45.290 --> 00:02:48.025
<i>- One older than any oath.</i>
- (dog barking)

16
00:02:48.026 --> 00:02:49.955
<i>Since the days of the First Men.</i>

17
00:02:49.956 --> 00:02:52.429
<i>we have stood as guardians</i>

18
00:02:52.430 --> 00:02:54.203
<i>against the cold and the dark.</i>

19
00:02:55.735 --> 00:02:57.501
<i>Through its long tradition.</i>

20
00:02:57.502 --> 00:02:59.765
<i>the Night's Watch
cultivated its strength</i>

21
00:02:59.766 --> 00:03:01.338
<i>from doomed men</i>

22
00:03:01.339 --> 00:03:04.008
<i>who had their life as
their only possession.</i>

23
00:03:04.009 --> 00:03:06.809
<i>But my ancestor. Torrhen Stark.</i>

24
00:03:06.810 --> 00:03:08.879
<i>began a tradition by
making an offering</i>

25
00:03:08.880 --> 00:03:11.348
<i>at the onset of winter:</i>

26
00:03:11.349 --> 00:03:13.650
<i>one in 10 men from our household</i>

27
00:03:13.651 --> 00:03:16.725
<i>was to be chosen to
fortify the Watch.</i>

28
00:03:19.526 --> 00:03:24.861
<i>This is not a
sentence but an honor.</i>

29
00:03:24.862 --> 00:03:28.999
<i>A duty embraced by all
who serve the North.</i>

30
00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.235
<i>Even by mine own kin.</i>

31
00:03:31.236 --> 00:03:33.538
♪

32
00:03:33.539 --> 00:03:35.577
(wind blowing)

33
00:03:36.410 --> 00:03:38.847
<i>The North must stand ready.</i>

34
00:03:40.213 --> 00:03:41.846
<i>Winter is coming.</i>

35
00:03:41.847 --> 00:03:44.080
Coming? What is this. then.

36
00:03:44.081 --> 00:03:46.083
that falls from the skies
and shivers my bones?

37
00:03:46.084 --> 00:03:49.853
This is only a late
summer snow. my prince.

38
00:03:49.854 --> 00:03:52.356
In winter. it will
cover all you see.

39
00:03:52.357 --> 00:03:54.763
and all memories of
warmth will be forgotten.

40
00:03:55.896 --> 00:03:58.095
It pleases me to think
that over a century ago

41
00:03:58.096 --> 00:04:00.769
our ancestors treated
in this very place.

42
00:04:02.136 --> 00:04:04.106
The Conqueror and the
King in the North.

43
00:04:05.873 --> 00:04:07.604
You. at least. had the mercy

44
00:04:07.605 --> 00:04:10.007
not to threaten me
with your dragon.

45
00:04:10.008 --> 00:04:12.247
(lift creaks loudly)

46
00:04:16.150 --> 00:04:18.182
(distant shouting)

47
00:04:18.183 --> 00:04:19.321
My prince.

48
00:04:20.120 --> 00:04:22.091
- My lord.
- My lord.

49
00:04:22.957 --> 00:04:24.254
M'lord.

50
00:04:24.255 --> 00:04:26.623
Surely the great Torrhen Stark

51
00:04:26.624 --> 00:04:29.560
would've sooner died
than bent the knee.

52
00:04:29.561 --> 00:04:30.794
Unless he believed the Conqueror

53
00:04:30.795 --> 00:04:33.135
could bring unity to
the Seven Kingdoms.

54
00:04:34.434 --> 00:04:36.199
You are right in that.

55
00:04:36.200 --> 00:04:39.303
That unity is now threatened.

56
00:04:39.304 --> 00:04:41.967
The realm will soon
tear itself apart...

57
00:04:41.968 --> 00:04:43.040
if men do not remember

58
00:04:43.041 --> 00:04:44.779
the oath sworn to King Viserys

59
00:04:45.145 --> 00:04:47.377
and to his rightful heir.

60
00:04:47.378 --> 00:04:50.885
Starks do not forget
their oaths. my prince.

61
00:04:51.418 --> 00:04:53.750
But you must know
that my gaze is

62
00:04:53.751 --> 00:04:57.288
forever torn between
north and south.

63
00:04:57.289 --> 00:05:00.657
In winter. my duty to the
Wall is even more dire

64
00:05:00.658 --> 00:05:02.459
than the one I owe
to King's Landing.

65
00:05:02.460 --> 00:05:04.728
I need my men here.

66
00:05:04.729 --> 00:05:05.958
Whilst your men guard against

67
00:05:05.959 --> 00:05:07.731
wildlings and weather.

68
00:05:07.732 --> 00:05:11.235
the Hightowers plan
to usurp the throne.

69
00:05:11.236 --> 00:05:13.470
If my mother is to
defend her claim

70
00:05:13.471 --> 00:05:14.772
to hold the realm united.

71
00:05:14.773 --> 00:05:16.140
she needs an army.

72
00:05:16.141 --> 00:05:17.174
War is coming

73
00:05:17.175 --> 00:05:19.276
to the whole of
the realm. my lord.

74
00:05:19.277 --> 00:05:22.151
We cannot wage it without
the support of the North.

75
00:05:23.150 --> 00:05:25.154
(wind blowing)

76
00:05:30.190 --> 00:05:32.189
My father brought King Jaehaerys

77
00:05:32.190 --> 00:05:34.462
and Queen Alysanne
to see the Wall.

78
00:05:35.162 --> 00:05:37.828
His Grace stood at
this very outlook

79
00:05:37.829 --> 00:05:39.930
and watched as their dragons.

80
00:05:39.931 --> 00:05:42.465
the greatest power in the world.

81
00:05:42.466 --> 00:05:44.506
refused to cross it.

82
00:05:46.140 --> 00:05:47.972
Do you think my ancestors built

83
00:05:47.973 --> 00:05:50.007
a 700-foot wall of ice

84
00:05:50.008 --> 00:05:52.481
to keep out snow and savages?

85
00:05:53.147 --> 00:05:54.983
What does it keep out?

86
00:05:57.017 --> 00:05:58.448
Death.

87
00:05:58.449 --> 00:06:01.690
(light. tense music playing)

88
00:06:06.360 --> 00:06:08.559
I have thousands of graybeards

89
00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:11.028
who've already seen
too many winters.

90
00:06:11.029 --> 00:06:14.398
They are... well-honed.

91
00:06:14.399 --> 00:06:16.070
So they're old?

92
00:06:16.938 --> 00:06:19.804
I can ready them
to march at once.

93
00:06:19.805 --> 00:06:21.171
If your graybeards can fight.

94
00:06:21.172 --> 00:06:23.474
the queen will have them.

95
00:06:23.475 --> 00:06:25.375
They will fight hard.

96
00:06:25.376 --> 00:06:27.139
Like Northerners.

97
00:06:27.140 --> 00:06:28.312
Stark captain: My lord?

98
00:06:28.313 --> 00:06:31.515
- (footsteps approaching)
- A raven's arrived.

99
00:06:31.516 --> 00:06:33.455
Urgent news from Dragonstone.

100
00:06:46.300 --> 00:06:49.304
(tense music playing)

101
00:06:53.107 --> 00:06:54.743
(roars)

102
00:07:01.148 --> 00:07:02.784
(Meleys roars)

103
00:07:07.221 --> 00:07:09.223
(Rhaenys speaks High Valyrian)

104
00:07:09.589 --> 00:07:11.593
(dragonkeeper speaks
High Valyrian)

105
00:07:15.962 --> 00:07:19.334
Take your mount again.
We're flying out.

106
00:07:22.001 --> 00:07:25.602
I alone patrol over a
hundred miles of open sea.

107
00:07:25.603 --> 00:07:29.373
endlessly. to hold the blockade.

108
00:07:29.374 --> 00:07:32.914
Meleys must gorge
and rest. as must I.

109
00:07:34.415 --> 00:07:36.914
- We're going to King's Landing.
- To what end?

110
00:07:36.915 --> 00:07:38.482
Killing Vhagar.

111
00:07:38.483 --> 00:07:41.552
I cannot face that
hoary old bitch alone.

112
00:07:41.553 --> 00:07:43.086
With my dragon and
yours together.

113
00:07:43.087 --> 00:07:45.723
we can kill Vhagar
and her rider.

114
00:07:45.724 --> 00:07:47.028
Make it a son for a son.

115
00:07:49.363 --> 00:07:52.062
- Was this the queen's command?
- The queen remains absent.

116
00:07:52.063 --> 00:07:54.096
I should be at
Harrenhal bending knees.

117
00:07:54.097 --> 00:07:56.800
but I must instead remain
here to wage her war.

118
00:07:56.801 --> 00:07:59.469
Or perhaps. more simply.
to await her return.

119
00:07:59.470 --> 00:08:02.839
She has been gone for days.
Too long. She is exposed.

120
00:08:02.840 --> 00:08:05.142
- She is grieving.
- The mother grieves

121
00:08:05.143 --> 00:08:07.549
as the queen shirks her duties.

122
00:08:09.483 --> 00:08:12.787
It was a raven that brought
me news of Laena's death.

123
00:08:13.787 --> 00:08:15.957
I existed for
weeks in torment...

124
00:08:17.024 --> 00:08:19.961
refusing to believe
what I'd been told.

125
00:08:21.962 --> 00:08:24.695
It was only when I saw my
daughter's mortal remains

126
00:08:24.696 --> 00:08:27.169
that I could begin to mourn her.

127
00:08:29.503 --> 00:08:33.142
A raven has told Rhaenyra
that her son is dead.

128
00:08:34.307 --> 00:08:35.806
She needs to know
it for certain.

129
00:08:35.807 --> 00:08:37.879
She was a fool to go alone.

130
00:08:38.645 --> 00:08:40.277
What if Aemond were
to happen upon her?

131
00:08:40.278 --> 00:08:42.083
Then I would pity Aemond.

132
00:08:44.718 --> 00:08:46.916
The queen was wise
to recuse herself.

133
00:08:48.015 --> 00:08:52.060
She has not acted on the vengeful
impulse that others might have.

134
00:08:53.427 --> 00:08:56.627
If you'd have acted when
you had the chance...

135
00:08:56.628 --> 00:08:59.268
Aegon's line would
be extinguished.

136
00:09:00.601 --> 00:09:02.871
And Luke would be alive.

137
00:09:10.044 --> 00:09:11.679
Fly with me.

138
00:09:12.446 --> 00:09:16.017
- It is a command.
- Would that you were the king.

139
00:09:19.586 --> 00:09:22.586
(solemn music playing)

140
00:09:22.587 --> 00:09:24.626
(dragons calling)

141
00:09:35.469 --> 00:09:38.473
♪

142
00:09:46.441 --> 00:09:49.651
(workers chattering. shouting)

143
00:09:53.281 --> 00:09:55.290
(animals chattering)

144
00:10:07.434 --> 00:10:09.638
(people greeting Corlys)

145
00:10:25.853 --> 00:10:26.988
M'lord.

146
00:10:29.789 --> 00:10:33.027
It's a marvel she was able to
return from the Stepstones at all.

147
00:10:35.423 --> 00:10:37.232
Barely done. but done.

148
00:10:37.664 --> 00:10:41.431
Seven more ships put out to sea
this morn' to fortify the blockade.

149
00:10:41.432 --> 00:10:43.834
The Gullet is vast. and we're
not like to have the numbers

150
00:10:43.835 --> 00:10:46.108
to cover all that open water.

151
00:10:48.803 --> 00:10:50.642
Corlys Velaryon: I must
have my ship back at sea

152
00:10:50.643 --> 00:10:52.008
to lead the effort.

153
00:10:52.009 --> 00:10:54.683
Alyn of Hull: It'll be
many weeks yet. I'd wager.

154
00:10:56.516 --> 00:10:58.981
But I'll have a word
with my brother...

155
00:10:58.982 --> 00:11:02.224
to see what reinforcements
the shipwrights can muster.

156
00:11:12.166 --> 00:11:14.836
The smithy delivered
this earlier.

157
00:11:17.004 --> 00:11:18.207
M'lord?

158
00:11:26.880 --> 00:11:29.879
I had this commissioned
for Prince Lucerys.

159
00:11:32.184 --> 00:11:35.156
I was very sorry to hear
about your heir's death.

160
00:11:35.689 --> 00:11:37.692
'Twas the blackest
of treacheries.

161
00:11:40.993 --> 00:11:45.829
Pardon. m'lord. if it'll
please you. much to do.

162
00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:47.064
They tell me that
you are the one

163
00:11:47.065 --> 00:11:49.204
that dragged my
body out of the sea.

164
00:11:54.574 --> 00:11:56.211
It was only my duty.

165
00:12:00.747 --> 00:12:03.885
I am indebted to you. Alyn.

166
00:12:16.030 --> 00:12:19.229
(light. tense music playing)

167
00:12:19.230 --> 00:12:21.903
(ambient nature sounds)

168
00:12:30.077 --> 00:12:32.080
♪

169
00:12:36.984 --> 00:12:39.621
- (indistinct chatter)
- (horse neighs)

170
00:12:41.155 --> 00:12:43.190
(soldier shouting)

171
00:12:43.457 --> 00:12:45.094
Mind your posts!

172
00:12:47.995 --> 00:12:49.998
Keep your focus. men!

173
00:12:53.600 --> 00:12:56.100
- Guard 1 (shouts): Dragon!
- Guard 2 (shouts): Dragon!

174
00:12:56.101 --> 00:12:57.734
Arm the scorpion!

175
00:12:57.735 --> 00:12:59.969
Guard 1 (shouts):
Arm the scorpion!

176
00:13:01.841 --> 00:13:04.241
Approaching from the southeast!

177
00:13:04.242 --> 00:13:05.542
Get around!

178
00:13:05.543 --> 00:13:07.449
- (scorpion creaking)
- (guard shouting)

179
00:13:09.983 --> 00:13:11.615
guard (shouts):
Scorpion ready!

180
00:13:11.616 --> 00:13:14.484
- Arryk Cargyll (shouts): Halt!
- Guard (shouts): Halt!

181
00:13:14.485 --> 00:13:16.720
(Vhagar grumbles)

182
00:13:16.721 --> 00:13:18.221
Stand down. it's Vhagar!

183
00:13:18.222 --> 00:13:20.091
Guard 2: Stand down!

184
00:13:20.092 --> 00:13:21.963
Guard 1: Standing down!

185
00:13:26.299 --> 00:13:28.303
(scorpion creaking)

186
00:13:30.337 --> 00:13:32.336
(Vhagar grumbles)

187
00:13:32.337 --> 00:13:34.376
(quiet chatter)

188
00:13:48.856 --> 00:13:50.692
Where is Jaehaerys?

189
00:13:52.026 --> 00:13:54.023
Attending his lessons.

190
00:13:54.829 --> 00:13:56.593
And those are where?

191
00:13:56.594 --> 00:13:58.095
What do you need of him?

192
00:13:58.096 --> 00:14:00.264
Taking him to the small council.

193
00:14:00.265 --> 00:14:01.298
He'll be king one day.

194
00:14:01.299 --> 00:14:03.237
He must begin his instruction.

195
00:14:03.637 --> 00:14:05.840
What if he does not
want to be king?

196
00:14:07.007 --> 00:14:08.333
(whispers) Where is he?

197
00:14:08.334 --> 00:14:09.471
The library.

198
00:14:09.837 --> 00:14:12.314
You must not
interrupt his custom.

199
00:14:19.053 --> 00:14:20.722
I'm afraid.

200
00:14:23.190 --> 00:14:24.391
Don't be.

201
00:14:25.091 --> 00:14:27.859
They'd be fools to come with
Vhagar protecting the city.

202
00:14:27.860 --> 00:14:29.898
Not the dragons.

203
00:14:30.765 --> 00:14:32.000
The rats.

204
00:14:41.008 --> 00:14:43.412
The queen is an
enduring mystery...

205
00:14:44.178 --> 00:14:45.580
is she not?

206
00:14:50.417 --> 00:14:52.421
(birds chirping)

207
00:14:54.922 --> 00:14:56.925
(heavy breathing)

208
00:14:58.125 --> 00:15:00.195
(quiet moaning)

209
00:15:09.937 --> 00:15:11.906
(birds cawing)

210
00:15:19.446 --> 00:15:21.216
There's a chill in the air.

211
00:15:25.485 --> 00:15:27.722
Summer is well
and truly through.

212
00:15:29.223 --> 00:15:32.060
We are expected at the
small council. Your Grace.

213
00:15:47.742 --> 00:15:49.139
We cannot.

214
00:15:49.844 --> 00:15:51.079
Again.

215
00:15:54.081 --> 00:15:55.684
Yes. Your Grace.

216
00:16:00.421 --> 00:16:02.424
If you wouldn't mind?

217
00:16:06.794 --> 00:16:09.798
(light music playing)

218
00:16:20.440 --> 00:16:22.444
(dog whimpers)

219
00:16:23.677 --> 00:16:25.680
♪

220
00:16:35.456 --> 00:16:37.855
- Tyland Lannister: Your Grace.
- Alicent Hightower: Good day.

221
00:16:37.856 --> 00:16:39.894
♪

222
00:16:42.228 --> 00:16:44.595
Aegon Targaryen: Hello! Jaehaerys
must learn the ways of the court

223
00:16:44.596 --> 00:16:46.631
if he is to rule
one day. (laughs)

224
00:16:46.632 --> 00:16:48.870
Up we go. (laughs)

225
00:16:49.837 --> 00:16:52.269
Good morrow. my lords.

226
00:16:52.270 --> 00:16:53.275
Mother.

227
00:16:55.476 --> 00:16:57.302
What news?

228
00:16:57.303 --> 00:16:59.844
Otto Hightower: Our letters
to the Vale and to the North

229
00:16:59.845 --> 00:17:02.050
continue to go unanswered.

230
00:17:02.650 --> 00:17:03.652
Cunts.

231
00:17:05.319 --> 00:17:07.684
Otto: The Stormlands
should be ours

232
00:17:07.685 --> 00:17:09.386
after Prince Aemond's
marriage pact

233
00:17:09.387 --> 00:17:11.654
to the Lady Floris Baratheon.

234
00:17:11.655 --> 00:17:13.857
I anticipate their
sworn declaration.

235
00:17:13.858 --> 00:17:17.962
(sighs) My brother is raising
the strength of the West

236
00:17:17.963 --> 00:17:21.065
to mass at the Golden
Tooth. but we...

237
00:17:21.066 --> 00:17:22.733
Yeah. thank you. my prince.

238
00:17:22.734 --> 00:17:25.169
That's. that's very helpful.

239
00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:26.703
My nephew. Lord Ormund.

240
00:17:26.704 --> 00:17:29.974
musters his forces to
sally forth from Oldtown.

241
00:17:29.975 --> 00:17:31.508
They expect to march quickly.

242
00:17:31.509 --> 00:17:35.011
meeting little resistance.
until they reach the Riverlands.

243
00:17:35.012 --> 00:17:36.981
My letters to Rhaenyra.
Has there been any answer?

244
00:17:36.982 --> 00:17:39.678
An apology for her dead son?

245
00:17:39.679 --> 00:17:41.218
None. Your Grace.

246
00:17:41.219 --> 00:17:43.486
Between that and their
blockade of the Gullet.

247
00:17:43.487 --> 00:17:45.523
we must presume that
the princess has refused

248
00:17:45.524 --> 00:17:47.057
the offered terms.

249
00:17:47.058 --> 00:17:49.693
and that war is now inevitable.

250
00:17:49.694 --> 00:17:51.662
- Jaehaerys Targaryen: Na-na!
- Perhaps Your Grace might lend

251
00:17:51.663 --> 00:17:53.968
- his voice to our outreach...
- Tyland: Stop! Enough!

252
00:17:54.701 --> 00:17:57.101
In hopes that new terms
might. might be negotiated.

253
00:17:57.102 --> 00:18:00.003
Release it at once!
Would someone please?

254
00:18:00.004 --> 00:18:02.944
Is the heir to the throne
bothering you. Tyland?

255
00:18:04.444 --> 00:18:08.079
No. No. no. not. not in
the least. Your Grace.

256
00:18:08.080 --> 00:18:10.547
Because I think he wants a ride.

257
00:18:10.548 --> 00:18:11.782
- Alicent: Your Grace.
- Tyland: Uh. a ride?

258
00:18:11.783 --> 00:18:13.350
A pony ride.

259
00:18:13.351 --> 00:18:14.951
Wouldn't that be fun. Jaehaerys?

260
00:18:14.952 --> 00:18:17.421
Should the Master of
Coin be your royal steed?

261
00:18:17.422 --> 00:18:19.228
(light laughter)

262
00:18:26.601 --> 00:18:28.898
Your Grace!

263
00:18:28.899 --> 00:18:31.140
There are important
matters to discuss...

264
00:18:32.573 --> 00:18:34.409
despite Sir Tyland's
interruptions.

265
00:18:35.943 --> 00:18:38.075
Aegon: Very well.

266
00:18:38.076 --> 00:18:40.515
No time for amusements. Tyland.

267
00:18:41.949 --> 00:18:43.152
Your Grace.

268
00:18:44.246 --> 00:18:46.655
Aegon: Off you go.
Jaehaerys. Good boy.

269
00:18:49.156 --> 00:18:50.792
Where were we? (clears throat)

270
00:18:52.291 --> 00:18:56.493
Rhaenyra's blockade has placed
King's Landing under strain.

271
00:18:56.494 --> 00:18:58.895
And those pressures
will multiply quickly.

272
00:18:58.896 --> 00:19:00.930
Well. we should've just killed
her when we had the chance.

273
00:19:00.931 --> 00:19:04.634
Regrettably. the opportunity
for surprise has been lost.

274
00:19:04.635 --> 00:19:08.338
and with it. the chance to
end this conflict quickly.

275
00:19:09.709 --> 00:19:11.808
We must play the
board before us.

276
00:19:11.809 --> 00:19:14.477
Tyland: If we are to break
the Sea Snake's blockade.

277
00:19:14.478 --> 00:19:17.181
we will need to bolster both the
Lannister and Hightower navies.

278
00:19:17.182 --> 00:19:19.916
We do have need for a
new Master of Ships.

279
00:19:19.917 --> 00:19:23.253
We could offer the title to
the young Lord Dalton Greyjoy.

280
00:19:23.254 --> 00:19:25.456
Aemond. What is
your business here?

281
00:19:25.457 --> 00:19:26.689
The king summoned me.

282
00:19:26.690 --> 00:19:28.491
You do not have a
seat at this council.

283
00:19:28.492 --> 00:19:31.796
Aemond is my closest
blood and our best sword.

284
00:19:31.797 --> 00:19:33.267
I welcome him.

285
00:19:33.967 --> 00:19:36.967
Path to King's Landing is
through the Riverlands.

286
00:19:36.968 --> 00:19:40.637
We must establish a toehold
there. at Harrenhal.

287
00:19:40.638 --> 00:19:42.639
Aegon: The Riverlords will
either declare for me.

288
00:19:42.640 --> 00:19:45.676
or they will meet Vhagar
and Sunfyre together.

289
00:19:45.677 --> 00:19:48.011
Ah. and-and we can burn the
blockade while we're at it.

290
00:19:48.012 --> 00:19:49.979
- Rhaenyra has dragons as well.
- Mine are bigger.

291
00:19:49.980 --> 00:19:52.449
If we lose the dragons to war.
there'll be no calling them back.

292
00:19:52.450 --> 00:19:54.050
- We must proceed cautiously.
- No.

293
00:19:54.051 --> 00:19:58.189
Fat. old Lord Tully will either
raise my banner or see his burn.

294
00:19:58.190 --> 00:20:00.294
We should fly to Riverrun.

295
00:20:00.727 --> 00:20:02.359
You are the king. Your Grace.

296
00:20:02.360 --> 00:20:03.860
You must not put
yourself at risk.

297
00:20:03.861 --> 00:20:06.630
And Vhagar is needed here to
deter Rhaenyra from attacking

298
00:20:06.631 --> 00:20:09.304
in retribution for
the death of her son.

299
00:20:10.337 --> 00:20:14.672
Errors were made in the hours
following King Viserys's death.

300
00:20:14.673 --> 00:20:16.911
We mustn't compound them.

301
00:20:18.512 --> 00:20:21.144
You've already demonstrated
your might. Your Grace.

302
00:20:21.145 --> 00:20:25.482
- We must now favor patience and restraint.
- (Aegon sighs)

303
00:20:25.483 --> 00:20:27.251
I send ravens by the hour.

304
00:20:27.252 --> 00:20:31.655
Many and more houses will
declare for you in time.

305
00:20:31.656 --> 00:20:34.829
History and precedent
will come to your side.

306
00:20:35.595 --> 00:20:38.233
- (birds chirping)
- (indistinct chatter)

307
00:20:42.602 --> 00:20:43.834
Good morrow. Your Grace.

308
00:20:43.835 --> 00:20:45.502
Good morrow. Lord Larys.

309
00:20:45.503 --> 00:20:47.404
I had come earlier
to have a word

310
00:20:47.405 --> 00:20:49.239
before the small
council convened.

311
00:20:49.240 --> 00:20:53.782
but your handmaiden said
that you were indisposed.

312
00:20:57.051 --> 00:20:59.154
What is it you wish to discuss?

313
00:21:01.120 --> 00:21:04.559
I have completed questioning
the whole of the castle staff.

314
00:21:05.725 --> 00:21:07.558
They produced rather
interesting details.

315
00:21:07.559 --> 00:21:12.234
but I am satisfied I have exposed
all who betrayed our trust.

316
00:21:14.068 --> 00:21:15.270
And what of them?

317
00:21:16.736 --> 00:21:18.940
They no longer breathe our air.

318
00:21:21.108 --> 00:21:24.746
I have chosen your
new staff personally.

319
00:21:29.784 --> 00:21:31.420
(door opens)

320
00:21:32.753 --> 00:21:34.356
(door closes)

321
00:21:43.130 --> 00:21:45.462
St... Gi-Give me that.

322
00:21:45.463 --> 00:21:47.398
Maidservant: Your Grace?

323
00:21:47.399 --> 00:21:49.438
(sighs) Just leave me.

324
00:21:51.104 --> 00:21:53.142
Just le... Just
le... Just leave me.

325
00:21:56.944 --> 00:21:58.575
(door opens)

326
00:21:58.576 --> 00:22:01.412
(tense. pensive music playing)

327
00:22:01.413 --> 00:22:02.617
(door closes)

328
00:22:12.225 --> 00:22:13.658
♪

329
00:22:13.659 --> 00:22:15.330
(Syrax roars)

330
00:22:30.644 --> 00:22:32.647
♪

331
00:22:34.315 --> 00:22:35.946
(indistinct shouting)

332
00:22:35.947 --> 00:22:38.153
- It's a dragon wing!
- Let's have a look!

333
00:22:39.753 --> 00:22:41.756
- It's a wing.
- Who cares what it is.

334
00:22:42.690 --> 00:22:44.321
(yells) Dragon!

335
00:22:44.322 --> 00:22:46.361
(crowd yelling)

336
00:22:47.427 --> 00:22:49.063
(Syrax roars)

337
00:22:51.264 --> 00:22:53.502
(yelling. panicking)

338
00:22:57.572 --> 00:22:59.208
(roars)

339
00:23:05.579 --> 00:23:08.578
(solemn music playing)

340
00:23:32.806 --> 00:23:34.833
♪

341
00:23:34.834 --> 00:23:36.478
(crying)

342
00:23:53.994 --> 00:23:55.997
(Syrax grumbling)

343
00:24:00.568 --> 00:24:03.572
♪

344
00:24:09.176 --> 00:24:11.041
(Syrax roars)

345
00:24:11.042 --> 00:24:14.244
Leon Estermont: All
hail King Aegon!

346
00:24:14.245 --> 00:24:16.713
"Aegon the Magnanimous."

347
00:24:16.714 --> 00:24:19.416
Second of His Name.
King of the Andals.

348
00:24:19.417 --> 00:24:21.779
and the Rhoynar.
and the First Men.

349
00:24:21.780 --> 00:24:25.056
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

350
00:24:25.057 --> 00:24:27.096
Hail King Aegon!

351
00:24:27.795 --> 00:24:29.431
"The Magnanimous"?

352
00:24:33.133 --> 00:24:34.368
Your Grace.

353
00:24:34.967 --> 00:24:38.006
Let's have the first
petition. my good Lord Hand.

354
00:24:39.707 --> 00:24:40.775
(grunts)

355
00:24:42.442 --> 00:24:44.275
(nervously) Good morrow.
my. uh. Your Grace.

356
00:24:44.276 --> 00:24:45.642
- (laughter)
- Aegon: It's alright.

357
00:24:45.643 --> 00:24:47.745
There's no reason to be nervous.

358
00:24:47.746 --> 00:24:48.913
What's your name?

359
00:24:48.914 --> 00:24:51.148
Gr... Uh. Jerard. Your Grace.

360
00:24:51.149 --> 00:24:53.250
Good morrow. Jerard.

361
00:24:53.251 --> 00:24:55.853
And how might your
king be of service?

362
00:24:55.854 --> 00:24:57.559
'Tis my flock.

363
00:24:58.559 --> 00:25:02.197
Uh. a-a-a tenth of
them taken by...

364
00:25:04.197 --> 00:25:07.131
- the Crown on...
- (crowd murmuring)

365
00:25:07.132 --> 00:25:09.366
on the cusp of winter.

366
00:25:09.367 --> 00:25:12.374
- If I'd had the time to plan...
- We should return them.

367
00:25:15.475 --> 00:25:16.974
- Your Grace?
- Aegon: Well. you need

368
00:25:16.975 --> 00:25:18.609
your goats for the
winter. don't you?

369
00:25:18.610 --> 00:25:21.445
- Sheep. Your-Your Grace.
- Aegon: Sheep. even better.

370
00:25:21.446 --> 00:25:23.815
I shall make your
flock of sheep whole.

371
00:25:23.816 --> 00:25:25.615
(Jerard laughs)

372
00:25:25.616 --> 00:25:28.119
We already made a promise
to all the Crownlands

373
00:25:28.120 --> 00:25:30.515
that a tithing of livestock

374
00:25:30.516 --> 00:25:32.790
would be necessary to
sustain the dragons

375
00:25:32.791 --> 00:25:34.224
for their increased activity

376
00:25:34.225 --> 00:25:37.266
and. pray not.
eventual fighting.

377
00:25:37.932 --> 00:25:40.030
Right... Right.

378
00:25:40.031 --> 00:25:43.065
Perhaps we could just return
his sheep. He came all this way.

379
00:25:43.066 --> 00:25:45.735
If you return one herder's
sheep. Your Grace.

380
00:25:45.736 --> 00:25:48.200
you will soon find them all
at the foot of your throne

381
00:25:48.201 --> 00:25:50.542
expecting the same.

382
00:25:50.543 --> 00:25:52.076
They won't know.

383
00:25:52.077 --> 00:25:58.077
When the king speaks.
Your Grace. all hear it.

384
00:26:06.926 --> 00:26:09.927
After further thought.
I have decided that

385
00:26:09.928 --> 00:26:12.390
I cannot restore your sheep.

386
00:26:12.391 --> 00:26:13.664
If war were to break out.

387
00:26:13.665 --> 00:26:15.566
my dragons will require feed.

388
00:26:15.567 --> 00:26:18.401
- Bring the next.
- (crowd murmuring)

389
00:26:18.402 --> 00:26:22.072
guildmaster: Salts always run
scarce on the road to winter.

390
00:26:22.073 --> 00:26:23.107
Your Grace.

391
00:26:23.108 --> 00:26:25.009
We rely on ships from Essos

392
00:26:25.010 --> 00:26:26.543
for our supply.

393
00:26:26.544 --> 00:26:29.779
But now. with a blockade in
place and war threatening...

394
00:26:29.780 --> 00:26:31.848
Yeah. that treasonous
blockade won't last long.

395
00:26:31.849 --> 00:26:34.385
I plan to send Vhagar
to burn it to ash.

396
00:26:34.386 --> 00:26:35.686
Bring the next.

397
00:26:35.687 --> 00:26:37.759
(crowd murmuring)

398
00:26:39.727 --> 00:26:41.330
Hugh. Your Grace.

399
00:26:44.799 --> 00:26:46.297
The smiths are all proud

400
00:26:46.298 --> 00:26:48.570
to support Your Grace
against Rhaenyra.

401
00:26:52.306 --> 00:26:53.304
But?

402
00:26:53.305 --> 00:26:54.576
But...

403
00:26:56.277 --> 00:26:59.142
iron costs have grown.

404
00:26:59.143 --> 00:27:02.650
A lone scorpion
takes weeks to build.

405
00:27:03.417 --> 00:27:05.621
To put it simply.
we are struggling.

406
00:27:06.453 --> 00:27:10.922
If we could but have the Crown's
coin before we started work.

407
00:27:10.923 --> 00:27:12.922
it would bring great relief.

408
00:27:12.923 --> 00:27:16.265
Not just to me. but to all
the smiths serving your cause.

409
00:27:18.499 --> 00:27:19.701
(sighs)

410
00:27:20.834 --> 00:27:23.872
You shall be paid and paid well.

411
00:27:24.305 --> 00:27:26.570
My army cannot win a war
without your weapons.

412
00:27:26.571 --> 00:27:28.576
You should continue
their making.

413
00:27:28.975 --> 00:27:32.781
Our victory depends on the
efforts of the smallfolk.

414
00:27:35.182 --> 00:27:38.315
You have my most sincere
gratitude. Your Grace.

415
00:27:38.316 --> 00:27:40.355
Aegon: I'll hear
the next petition.

416
00:27:41.021 --> 00:27:43.024
(indistinct chatter)

417
00:27:47.961 --> 00:27:50.827
Larys Strong: Your Grace. it filled my
heart to see you on the Iron Throne.

418
00:27:50.828 --> 00:27:54.031
- (Aegon groans) - I was only a boy
when Jaehaerys last graced the seat.

419
00:27:54.032 --> 00:27:55.499
but you brought forth
memories of him.

420
00:27:55.500 --> 00:27:57.635
and you have such a deft
touch with the smallfolk.

421
00:27:57.636 --> 00:27:59.469
just as your father did.

422
00:27:59.470 --> 00:28:00.909
Thank you. my lord.

423
00:28:01.408 --> 00:28:03.645
I wonder. do you have a
moment for a quiet word?

424
00:28:09.716 --> 00:28:13.117
It is the Hand's wont to
keep a firm grip on things.

425
00:28:13.118 --> 00:28:14.156
Mm.

426
00:28:15.355 --> 00:28:17.259
He controlled your
father the same way.

427
00:28:19.025 --> 00:28:21.659
Viserys had a certain
reputation as being pliable.

428
00:28:21.660 --> 00:28:23.098
I am aware.

429
00:28:24.765 --> 00:28:27.131
I would think. as
we find ourselves

430
00:28:27.132 --> 00:28:29.366
standing within a
hair's breadth of war.

431
00:28:29.367 --> 00:28:32.274
that you would wish to
be viewed differently.

432
00:28:35.543 --> 00:28:36.907
How?

433
00:28:36.908 --> 00:28:38.613
Otto Hightower...

434
00:28:40.047 --> 00:28:42.984
was your father's
Hand. Your Grace.

435
00:28:59.600 --> 00:29:00.802
Daughter.

436
00:29:02.035 --> 00:29:04.639
I requested an
audience hours ago.

437
00:29:05.940 --> 00:29:09.778
There were many petitions.

438
00:29:12.445 --> 00:29:14.283
Alicent: I find
myself wondering...

439
00:29:15.448 --> 00:29:17.252
do we pursue the same end?

440
00:29:19.318 --> 00:29:22.757
I must admit. there are days
where I myself can't be sure.

441
00:29:24.491 --> 00:29:26.495
I shall tell you mine.

442
00:29:28.128 --> 00:29:29.626
It's victory.

443
00:29:29.627 --> 00:29:32.462
And how would you
define "victory"?

444
00:29:32.463 --> 00:29:34.431
Rhaenyra bending the knee

445
00:29:34.432 --> 00:29:37.071
and Aegon sitting the
Iron Throne. in peace.

446
00:29:37.838 --> 00:29:39.369
As Viserys wished.

447
00:29:39.370 --> 00:29:43.040
Well. if that's how you describe
it. then we are aligned.

448
00:29:43.041 --> 00:29:45.142
- Then be my ally.
- I am.

449
00:29:45.143 --> 00:29:46.944
An ally would not
repeatedly cut my legs

450
00:29:46.945 --> 00:29:48.979
from beneath me at
that table of men!

451
00:29:48.980 --> 00:29:52.649
- I sit there and I feel your anger.
- Frustration.

452
00:29:52.650 --> 00:29:55.118
These critical days
since Viserys's passing

453
00:29:55.119 --> 00:29:57.987
- haven't gone to plan.
- That's not my fault.

454
00:29:59.526 --> 00:30:02.559
My sons both see you
as the great example.

455
00:30:02.560 --> 00:30:03.765
The Hand to three kings.

456
00:30:05.499 --> 00:30:07.331
Aegon is ever-eager
to prove himself

457
00:30:07.332 --> 00:30:08.803
and Aemond...

458
00:30:10.432 --> 00:30:12.040
Aemond is angry.

459
00:30:13.607 --> 00:30:16.239
Rhaenyra's son took his eye
and was never punished for it.

460
00:30:16.240 --> 00:30:20.882
- What he did. however vicious...
- The caprice of youth.

461
00:30:24.952 --> 00:30:26.784
I could only hope.

462
00:30:26.785 --> 00:30:29.953
Aemond erred.

463
00:30:29.954 --> 00:30:33.457
But he is fiercely loyal.
He wishes to please.

464
00:30:33.458 --> 00:30:35.126
And Aegon still heeds me.

465
00:30:35.127 --> 00:30:36.731
In private. at least.

466
00:30:38.298 --> 00:30:39.696
But if you undermine my voice.

467
00:30:39.697 --> 00:30:41.526
both those boys will
grow deaf to it.

468
00:30:41.527 --> 00:30:44.573
(light music playing)

469
00:30:49.977 --> 00:30:52.375
I hadn't seen it that way.

470
00:30:52.376 --> 00:30:54.444
We only need to mind Aegon

471
00:30:54.445 --> 00:30:56.684
until the novelty
of rule is spent.

472
00:30:57.584 --> 00:31:00.718
Once he tires of it. you and I
can steer our cause to victory.

473
00:31:00.719 --> 00:31:03.391
A fine strategy. daughter.

474
00:31:04.057 --> 00:31:09.698
But you must accept that the path
to victory now is one of violence.

475
00:31:10.698 --> 00:31:12.334
I know it.

476
00:31:16.070 --> 00:31:18.273
But that does not mean
it must be wanton.

477
00:31:20.608 --> 00:31:21.610
No.

478
00:31:25.680 --> 00:31:28.683
(tense music playing)

479
00:31:35.189 --> 00:31:37.192
(indistinct shouting)

480
00:31:38.425 --> 00:31:40.695
solider (shouts):
Prepare to be boarded!

481
00:31:43.297 --> 00:31:46.496
By the order of Lord
Corlys Velaryon!

482
00:31:46.497 --> 00:31:49.166
Erryk Cargyll: Search
the hold for stowaways!

483
00:31:49.167 --> 00:31:51.206
♪

484
00:31:57.078 --> 00:31:59.080
(indistinct shouting)

485
00:32:07.555 --> 00:32:09.186
(goats bleating)

486
00:32:09.187 --> 00:32:11.226
(music fades out)

487
00:32:16.730 --> 00:32:17.732
You.

488
00:32:20.267 --> 00:32:23.472
When last we met.
there were two of you.

489
00:32:25.740 --> 00:32:27.238
"The White Worm."

490
00:32:27.239 --> 00:32:29.806
Mysaria: Did you think I
would wither in your absence?

491
00:32:29.807 --> 00:32:31.874
I did not think you
would flower a traitor.

492
00:32:31.875 --> 00:32:35.212
You speak of highborn
games. I am common-born.

493
00:32:35.213 --> 00:32:37.714
How long have you been selling
secrets to Otto Hightower?

494
00:32:37.715 --> 00:32:39.754
As long as he had
gold to pay for them.

495
00:32:42.122 --> 00:32:46.328
Who sent you fleeing from King's
Landing in such disrepair. hm?

496
00:32:47.856 --> 00:32:49.894
You put Aegon on the throne.

497
00:32:49.895 --> 00:32:51.995
That was the
Hightowers' conspiracy.

498
00:32:51.996 --> 00:32:54.564
I merely profited from
knowing Aegon's movements.

499
00:32:54.565 --> 00:32:56.132
But you delivered him.

500
00:32:56.133 --> 00:32:59.069
He would've returned home
eventually for gold and for respite.

501
00:32:59.070 --> 00:33:00.237
as he always does.

502
00:33:00.238 --> 00:33:03.340
I simply... simply sped
the business along.

503
00:33:03.341 --> 00:33:05.408
"Business" that ended with the
theft of the queen's throne

504
00:33:05.409 --> 00:33:06.643
and the murder of her son.

505
00:33:06.644 --> 00:33:08.613
You only blame me
because your true enemies

506
00:33:08.614 --> 00:33:10.285
are out of reach.

507
00:33:11.814 --> 00:33:13.250
My arrangement with the Hand

508
00:33:13.251 --> 00:33:14.818
was purely transactional.

509
00:33:14.819 --> 00:33:16.791
I held no loyalty to him.

510
00:33:17.457 --> 00:33:19.393
Certainly do not now.

511
00:33:19.992 --> 00:33:24.761
Otto Hightower was to me as I am to
